@localBaseUrl@reviewBaseUrl@reviewAlbDnsName
# Default target for the collection.
# - Local Docker Compose: keep localBaseUrl.
# - Live mentor review after DNS works: change to reviewBaseUrl.
@baseUrl
# Live review notes:
# - Use HTTPS only. There is no HTTP listener for the review ALB.
# - Browser after DNS/CNAME:
#     https://api.lepomas.xyz/docs
#     https://api.lepomas.xyz/health
# - Before DNS/CNAME resolves locally, use curl with SNI preserved:
#     curl --connect-to api.lepomas.xyz:443:projectvault-api-review-299417498.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com:443 https://api.lepomas.xyz/health
#     curl -I --connect-to api.lepomas.xyz:443:projectvault-api-review-299417498.us-east-1.elb.amazonaws.com:443 https://api.lepomas.xyz/docs

# Optional sample data:
#   ./scripts/seed-sample-data.sh
#
# Seeded demo users:
#   ana / super-secret-123
#   bob / super-secret-123
#   carla / super-secret-123
#   diego / super-secret-123
#
# The seed script prints current project/document IDs.

# Paste access_token values from the login responses below.
@anaToken = paste-ana-access-token-here
@bobToken = paste-bob-access-token-here
@carlaToken = paste-carla-access-token-here
@diegoToken = paste-diego-access-token-here

# Paste IDs from API responses as you create them.
@projectId = paste-project-id-here
@bobUserId = paste-bob-user-id-here
@carlaUserId = paste-carla-user-id-here
@diegoUserId = paste-diego-user-id-here
@documentId = paste-document-id-here
@presignedDocumentId = paste-presigned-document-id-here
@presignedUploadUrl = paste-presigned-upload-url-here

### Live review - Health after DNS/CNAME
GET {{reviewBaseUrl}}/health

### Live review - Swagger UI after DNS/CNAME
GET {{reviewBaseUrl}}/docs

### Live review - OpenAPI JSON after DNS/CNAME
GET {{reviewBaseUrl}}/openapi.json


### Health - Estado del servicio
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Metadata - OpenAPI JSON
GET {{baseUrl}}/openapi.json

### Metadata - Swagger UI
GET {{baseUrl}}/docs

### Metadata - ReDoc
GET {{baseUrl}}/redoc


### Auth - Registrar Ana
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "ana",
  "email": "ana@example.com",
  "password": "super-secret-123",
  "repeat_password": "super-secret-123"
}

### Auth - Registrar Bob
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "login": "bob",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "password": "super-secret-123",
  "repeat_password": "super-secret-123"
}

### Auth - Registrar Carla
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

